# ===========================================
# COMMIT MESSAGE TEMPLATE
# ===========================================
# |-------- 45 characters --------|
# |-------------- 50 char limit -------------|
#
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types: feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|test|chore|perf|ci|build|revert
# Scope: api|mobile|ai|shared|deps|config (optional)
#
# Example: feat(mobile): add card creation screen

# --- SUBJECT LINE (max 50 chars) ---
# |-------- 45 characters --------|12345


# --- BODY (wrap at 72 characters) ---
# Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW - the code shows that)
# |---------------------------- 72 characters ----------------------------|


# --- FOOTER ---
# Reference issues: Fixes #123, Closes #456
# Breaking changes: BREAKING CHANGE: description


# ===========================================
# COMMIT MESSAGE CHECKLIST
# ===========================================
# Before committing, verify:
#
# [ ] Subject is in imperative mood ("Add" not "Added")
# [ ] Subject starts with lowercase after type
# [ ] Subject has no period at the end
# [ ] Subject is under 50 characters
# [ ] Body explains motivation and context
# [ ] Body wraps at 72 characters
# [ ] Related issues are referenced
# [ ] Breaking changes are documented
#
# ===========================================
# GOOD COMMIT MESSAGE EXAMPLES
# ===========================================
#
# feat(mobile): add spaced repetition scheduler
# 
# Implement FSRS algorithm for optimal card scheduling.
# Users can now benefit from scientifically-backed
# review intervals.
# 
# - Add FSRS v6.1.1 implementation
# - Create unified scheduler interface
# - Add card state management
# 
# Fixes #42
#
# -------------------------------------------
#
# fix(api): prevent duplicate study sessions
# 
# Users reported creating multiple sessions when
# rapidly tapping the start button.
# 
# Add debounce mechanism and database constraints
# to prevent race conditions.
# 
# Fixes #123
#
# -------------------------------------------
#
# docs: update API authentication guide
# 
# Add examples for JWT token refresh flow and
# error handling best practices.
#
